<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,403,264,291]" box="[189,403,264,291]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,403,264,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,403,264,291]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Descriptive notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1398,311,373]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
Wings with brownish darkening; hind wing with the angle between basal (
<emphasis box="[1063,1087,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">M</emphasis>
) and cubital (
<emphasis box="[1252,1286,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Cu</emphasis>
) veins ca 70°, costal margin with eight, nine or ten hamuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1400,412,579]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,412,438]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Female</emphasis>
Total body length 
<quantity box="[412,549,447,474]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.5">7.5–10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[568,659,447,473]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1972,1998]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1209,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-248@24.[189,1398,1209,1934]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 12. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). Habitus in lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705348/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Head transverse, ca 1.25 times as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1385,447,473]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
); vertex elevated with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus approximately two lateral ocellar diameters as seen in frontal view; labrum trapezoidal, 0.7 times as long as basal width; ocello-ocular area and vertex irregularly punctate with punctures separated by 0.5–4 puncture diameters;
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" startId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" targetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph blockId="25.[187,1399,1952,2014]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[187,282,1952,1978]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Fig. 13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bluthgen, 1927" authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[294,742,1952,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lasimensis">
<emphasis box="[294,548,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">Sphecodes lasimensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bluthgen P." box="[557,742,1952,1979]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♀ (PCMS). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[902,923,1952,1978]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">A</emphasis>
. Head in frontal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1205,1223,1953,1979]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">B</emphasis>
. Mesosoma in dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[338,359,1987,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="99">C</emphasis>
. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1400,265,468]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">
paraocular area with dense adpressed white pubescence, but not obscuring integument, gena with sparser pubescence. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum sparsely punctate (30–50 μm / 1–7); propodeal triangle (metapostnotum) and mesepisternum reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[958,1069,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Metasomal terga sparsely punctate, on discs with shallow tiny punctures separated by a few diameters (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1229,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[187,230,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-111@25.[189,1398,635,1907]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Sphecodes lasimensis Blüthgen, 1927, ♀ (PCMS). A. Head in frontal view. B. Mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Metasoma in dorsal view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705350/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); T1 marginal zone indistinctly punctate with a few tiny punctures; T2–T4 marginal zone smooth and impunctate; pygidial plate 0.5 times as wide as metabasitarsus; T1–T4 red, T5 partially brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1400,506,673]" box="[234,651,506,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,507,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Male</emphasis>
(according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bluthgen P." box="[468,643,506,533]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100" pagination="23 - 112" refId="ref17172" refString="Bluthgen P. 1927. Beitrage zur Systematik der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. III. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 53 (1 / 3): 23 - 112." type="journal article" year="1927">Blüthgen 1927</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1400,506,673]" pageId="26" pageNumber="100">Head weakly transverse, ca 1.15 times as wide as long; vertex elevated with distance from top of head to upper margin of lateral ocellus approximately two lateral ocellar diameters as seen in frontal view. Tyloids (from F4 onward) weakly developed, semicircular across basal 1/5–⅓ of ventral surface of flagellomeres.</paragraph>
